          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/537.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/537.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, slice the mushrooms thinly</p>\r\n<p><strong>Grate</strong> the cheese</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cut</strong> the potatoes into bite-size chunks</p>\r\n<p><strong>Trim</strong> the green beans and cut in half</p>\r\n<p><strong>Boil</strong> a kettle</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/537.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/537.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/537.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/537.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/537.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Once</strong> the onions are soft and brown, remove the lid and increase the heat to high to drive off any excess moisture</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> the mushrooms to the onions and cook for 5 min or until browned and all the liquid has evaporated, then remove the pan from the heat and season lightly with salt and pepper</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/537.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/537.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/537.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/537.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/537.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Spread</strong> the mustard over the cooled pork</p>\r\n<p><strong>Spoon</strong> the mushroom mixture on top, dividing it evenly between the pork steaks</p>\r\n<p><strong>Sprinkle</strong> with the panko breadcrumbs, grated cheese and paprika</p>\r\n<p><strong>Bake</strong> in the oven for 10-15 min or until a golden crust has formed and the pork is cooked through</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/537.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/537.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/537.-step-6-x700.jpg",
